        "Keywords": "carbon capture",
        "Description": "A post-combustion carbon capture unit using structured solid sorbents (MOFs) in a rotary adsorption machine (SVANTE VeloxoTherm RC-TSA process) that captures 90% of the CO2 from industrial flue gases via temperature swing adsorption, consuming 0.2 kWh/kgCO2 of electricity for the rotary machine. Captured CO2 is desorbed using low-pressure superheated steam (140°C, 1 bar, 0.8 MJ/kgCO2) yielding a CO2 product at 95 mol% purity, with the remaining 10% of CO2 released to the environment.",
        "DOI": "",
        "Main Related Publication": "Lin et al. (2021), https://doi.org/10.1126/science.abi7281",
        "References": "",
